<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,511,1259]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis box="[199,329,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body pale brown with numerous dark brown spots, striations on pronotum and head strong (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1. P" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[181,1398,205,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1408,195,1899]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. P. (P.) tribrachyblasta sp. nov. A, Body, dorsal view; B, Habitus, lateral view; C, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, Face. P. (P.) dentiforma sp. nov. E, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; F, Face; G, Body, dorsal view; H, Habitus, lateral view. P. (P.) dinghuensis sp. nov. I, Body, dorsal view; J, Habitus, lateral view; K, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; L, Face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225937/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
Figs. 
<number box="[151,163,584,608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="1.0">
<date box="[151,163,584,608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">1</date>
</number>
</figureCitation>
I, J). Ocelli white, eyes pale brown (
<figureCitation box="[568,631,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. P" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[181,1398,205,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1408,195,1899]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. P. (P.) tribrachyblasta sp. nov. A, Body, dorsal view; B, Habitus, lateral view; C, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, Face. P. (P.) dentiforma sp. nov. E, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; F, Face; G, Body, dorsal view; H, Habitus, lateral view. P. (P.) dinghuensis sp. nov. I, Body, dorsal view; J, Habitus, lateral view; K, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; L, Face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225937/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
Fig. 
<number box="[620,631,584,608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
L). Scutellum triangular, yellowish, with scattered dark notches, base of lateral sides yellow (
<figureCitation box="[384,447,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. P" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[181,1398,205,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1408,195,1899]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. P. (P.) tribrachyblasta sp. nov. A, Body, dorsal view; B, Habitus, lateral view; C, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, Face. P. (P.) dentiforma sp. nov. E, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; F, Face; G, Body, dorsal view; H, Habitus, lateral view. P. (P.) dinghuensis sp. nov. I, Body, dorsal view; J, Habitus, lateral view; K, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; L, Face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225937/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
Fig. 
<number box="[436,447,620,644]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
K). Forewing hyaline-brown, except basal and distal areas which are opaque chocolatebrown, venation fuscous spotted with white (
<figureCitation box="[655,718,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. P" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[181,1398,205,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1408,195,1899]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. P. (P.) tribrachyblasta sp. nov. A, Body, dorsal view; B, Habitus, lateral view; C, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, Face. P. (P.) dentiforma sp. nov. E, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; F, Face; G, Body, dorsal view; H, Habitus, lateral view. P. (P.) dinghuensis sp. nov. I, Body, dorsal view; J, Habitus, lateral view; K, Head and pronotum, dorsal view; L, Face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225937/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
Fig. 
<number box="[707,718,656,680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
J).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,511,1259]" box="[199,1178,692,721]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis box="[199,343,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">Morphology.</emphasis>
Body stout and small. Face shorter. 
<collectingCountry box="[751,807,692,717]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibial spinulation R 
<number box="[1028,1035,707,721]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="1.0">1</number>
<number box="[1035,1064,692,716]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="11.0">11</number>
, R 
<number box="[1095,1103,707,721]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="2.0">2</number>
<number box="[1102,1117,692,716]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="8.0">8</number>
, R 
<number box="[1149,1157,707,721]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="3.0">3</number>
<number box="[1157,1174,692,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="5.0">5</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,511,1259]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis box="[199,374,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[490,560,730,755]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[200,1384,207,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[190,1392,195,1918]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pedionis (Pedioni s) dinghuensis sp. nov. A, Pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, Connective, ventral view; C, Connective, lateral view; D, Aedeagus, caudal view; E, Aedeagus, lateral view; F, Dorsal connective, lateral view; G, Style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225940/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
Fig. 
<number box="[546,560,731,755]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A) with an obvious incision on dorsal margin, posterior half rather straight, caudo-dorsal angle with a small spine, several setae on ventral margin. Subgenital plate of uniform width, and with many setae, several especially long at the end. Style (
<figureCitation box="[759,827,802,827]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[200,1384,207,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[190,1392,195,1918]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pedionis (Pedioni s) dinghuensis sp. nov. A, Pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, Connective, ventral view; C, Connective, lateral view; D, Aedeagus, caudal view; E, Aedeagus, lateral view; F, Dorsal connective, lateral view; G, Style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225940/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
Fig. 
<number box="[813,827,803,827]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
G) parallel-margined and angled on apical third, apex obliquely truncate. Aedeagus shaft (
<figureCitation box="[580,664,838,863]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[200,1384,207,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[190,1392,195,1918]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pedionis (Pedioni s) dinghuensis sp. nov. A, Pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, Connective, ventral view; C, Connective, lateral view; D, Aedeagus, caudal view; E, Aedeagus, lateral view; F, Dorsal connective, lateral view; G, Style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225940/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
Figs. 
<number box="[649,664,839,863]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D, E) with 
<number box="[806,820,839,863]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="2.0">2</number>
paired processes, subapical slender, fingerlike ones ventrally directed. Dorsal connective (
<figureCitation box="[590,658,874,899]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[200,1384,207,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[190,1392,195,1918]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pedionis (Pedioni s) dinghuensis sp. nov. A, Pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, Connective, ventral view; C, Connective, lateral view; D, Aedeagus, caudal view; E, Aedeagus, lateral view; F, Dorsal connective, lateral view; G, Style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225940/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
Fig. 
<number box="[644,658,875,899]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
F) sinuate, with broad base, apical half slender, with serrated mesal edge and provided with basal fingerlike process.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,511,1259]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis box="[199,290,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">Female.</emphasis>
Body coloration and appearance similar to male. 
<number box="[855,868,946,971]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="7.0">7</number>
th sternite with posterior margin sinuated, midline about 
<number box="[220,255,982,1007]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times longer than 
<number box="[463,477,982,1007]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" value="6.0">6</number>
th, ovipositor strongly projecting beyond pygofer.
</paragraph>
