<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="594" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,511,1259]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1126,1151]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[325,567,1126,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dinghuensis">
<emphasis box="[325,567,1126,1151]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">Pedionis dinghuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Huang &amp; Viraktamath" authorityName="Huang &amp; Viraktamath" box="[700,1152,1126,1152]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufoscutellata">
<emphasis box="[700,887,1126,1151]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">P. rufoscutellata</emphasis>
Huang &amp; Viraktamath
</taxonomicName>
internally, but differs in having a pair of ventrally directed subapical aedeagal processes, and lacks falcate process on dorsal connective. 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufoscutellata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">P. rufoscutellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have processes perpendicular to shaft and have a large falcate medial process on dorsal connective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
